You are building a WooCommerce extension plugin.

Follow these rules strictly:

PLUGIN RULES
- Plugin prefix must be SSF_
- Namespace must be SSF\Wishlist
- No global functions allowed
- No anonymous functions in hooks
- Use class-based architecture
- Use singleton pattern for main plugin class

WORDPRESS CODING
- Follow WordPress coding standards
- Escape all outputs
- Sanitize all inputs
- Use nonces for AJAX
- No direct DB queries without $wpdb prepare

WOOCOMMERCE RULES
- Use WooCommerce session for guest wishlist
- Hook into WooCommerce actions only
- Do not override WooCommerce templates
- Load plugin only if WooCommerce active

DATABASE RULES
- Tables must use prefix: {$wpdb->prefix}SSF_
- Use dbDelta for table creation
- No postmeta storage

AJAX RULES
- Prefix AJAX actions with ssf_
- Must support logged and guest users
- Must return wp_send_json_success/error

ADMIN RULES
- Use WooCommerce settings API
- Minimal settings only
- No custom admin page

ASSET RULES
- Prefix handles with ssf-
- Load scripts only when needed
- Localize script for ajax_url and nonce

SECURITY
- check_ajax_referer required
- sanitize_text_field
- absint
- wp_unslash

PERFORMANCE
- No heavy queries on page load
- Use AJAX for wishlist actions
- Cache session owner
